OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1773501074
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 29 Mar to Sun 12 Apr
OL,6,FBlocked, or slowly evolving, weather
OL,7,Fpatterns are favoured for late March
OL,8,Finto early April, with high pressure
OL,9,Fprobably building to the north or
OL,10,Fnortheast of the UK. Whilst confidence
OL,11,Fis low in how this will influence the
OL,12,Fweather across the UK, this tends to
OL,13,Flead to a more prolonged period of a
OL,14,Fcertain weather type, be it settled or
OL,15,Funsettled. In any case, a reduction in
OL,16,FAtlantic-dominated weather patterns is
OL,17,Flikely, although some wet weather
OL,18,Fremains possible at times, perhaps
OL,19,Fmore especially in the south and east
OL,20,Fwhilst northwestern areas tend to be
OL,21,Fdrier than average. Temperatures will
OL,22,Fprobably be close to average for the
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fperiod as a whole, but there is an
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fincreased chance of some colder
OL,25,Fconditions developing for a time with
OL,26,Fa risk of frost.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
